Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  The Court sentenced the Defendant as follows:

As to Count #1: The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of TEN (10) YEARS; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is FIVE (5) YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is FIVE (5) YEARS.  
As to count #4:  The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of TEN (10) YEARS; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is FIVE (5) YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is FIVE (5) YEARS concurrent to count #1.

As to count #5:   The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of TEN (10) YEARS; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is FIVE (5) YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is FIVE (5) YEARS concurrent to count #4.

As to count #6:  The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of TEN (10) YEARS; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is FIVE (5) YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is FIVE (5) YEARS concurrent to count #5.

The Court imposed the following conditions of extended supervision FOR ALL COUNTS:  
1) Obtain an AODA assessment and successfully complete follow-up treatment; 
2) Maintain absolute sobriety with random urine screens - no illegal drugs; no controlled substances unless by valid prescription;
3) Obtain/maintain full-time employment, full-time school, or combination of both;
4) Pay supervision fees;
5) Provide a DNA sample - pay surcharge;
6)  Pay Restitution, joint and several (Antoniak 15CF732 and Vaggalis 15CF734) in the amounts of:  $245 to Speedway and $185.38 to McDonald's.
7)  The Defendant is to receive a credit of 49 days.

The defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program AND the Substance Abuse Program after 18 months.  The Defendant can be released after 30 days if successful.  

Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Body Armor and Voting.
